  "prompt": "How do I introduce myself in SSB interview?",
  "response": "Here's a structured approach to introducing yourself in an SSB (Services Selection Board) interview:\n\n1. Basic Personal Details:\n- Name\n- Father's name\n- Native place/hometown\n- Educational qualification\n- Current status (student/working professional)\n\n2. Family Background:\n- Brief information about parents' profession\n- Number of family members\n- Any family members in defense services (if applicable)\n\n3. Educational Achievements:\n- Academic qualifications\n- Percentage/grades\n- Special achievements/awards\n- Extra-curricular activities\n\n4. Personal Qualities:\n- Highlight your strengths\n- Leadership experiences\n- Team working abilities\n- Motivation for joining defense services\n\n5. Career Motivation:\n- Why you want to join defense services\n- Your understanding of defense role\n- Long-term career goals\n- Commitment to serve the nation\n\n6. Important Tips:\n- Be confident and natural\n- Speak clearly and maintain eye contact\n- Stay authentic\n- Avoid memorized speeches\n- Keep it crisp (2-3 minutes)\n- Positive body language\n- Smile and be enthusiastic\n\n7. Additional Suggestions:\n- Practice beforehand\n- Keep information genuine\n- Be prepared for follow-up questions\n\nRemember: Honesty and genuine passion are key.",
